<section id="command-reverse">
    <title>REVERSE</title>
<indexterm><primary>REVERSE</primary></indexterm>


<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>REVERSE</command> <parameter>thing</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs the reverse of its input.
</para>

<para>
If <parameter>thing</parameter> is a list, then REVERSE outputs a list with the same members in the reverse order.
</para>

<para>
If <parameter>thing</parameter> is a word, then REVERSE outputs a word with the same letters in the reverse order.
</para>

<para>
REVERSE throws an error if <parameter>thing</parameter> is an array.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SHOW REVERSE [1 2 3]</userinput>
[3 2 1]</programlisting>

<programlisting><userinput>SHOW REVERSE "abc</userinput>
cba</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
